## WSJF Scoring Model

**WSJF Score = (Business Value + Time Criticality + Risk Reduction) Ã· Job Size**

| Component | Scale | Definition |
|---|---|---|
| **Business Value** | 1â€“13 (Fibonacci) | Revenue impact, customer value, strategic alignment. 1 = marginal business impact; 13 = critical to enterprise strategy or major revenue driver |
| **Time Criticality** | 1â€“13 (Fibonacci) | Deadline pressure, cost of delay, competitive urgency. 1 = fully flexible timeline; 13 = immovable regulatory or contractual deadline |
| **Risk Reduction / Opportunity Enablement** | 1â€“13 (Fibonacci) | Technical risk reduction, platform enablement, unblocks other work. 1 = no risk reduction; 13 = eliminates critical technical debt or unblocks multiple initiatives |
| **Job Size** | 1â€“13 (Fibonacci) | Estimated effort in story points or person-days. 1 = trivial (&lt; 1 day); 13 = very large (&gt; 2 sprints of dedicated effort) |

**Scoring guidance:**

- Use Fibonacci values (1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13) to force meaningful differentiation.
- Score components independently â€” do not let one dimension influence another.
- A high WSJF score means the item delivers disproportionate value relative to its size.
- Items with Job Size = 1 should be scrutinised â€” they may be quick wins or may be under-estimated.

